155
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,679
I'm very touched by your words,

156
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:06,359
but we need to be realistic.

157
00:09:06,799 --> 00:09:07,640
Realistic?

158
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,039
It's not realistic?

159
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,400
Think about it.

160
00:09:12,039 --> 00:09:13,359
Always renting an apartment

161
00:09:14,080 --> 00:09:16,039
means to be constantly
chased by the owners.

162
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:18,400
Even if we have a touring car,

163
00:09:18,599 --> 00:09:20,799
we can't drive through oceans or rivers.

164
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:23,719
And do you think life will be easier

165
00:09:23,919 --> 00:09:25,599
if we become farmers in Australia?

166
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:27,280
No, it won't.

167
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:28,960
Because I would never

168
00:09:29,239 --> 00:09:31,359
let you touch cow dung

169
00:09:31,599 --> 00:09:32,840
or pull grass.

170
00:09:33,919 --> 00:09:35,159
Enough, He Qunfei.

171
00:09:35,799 --> 00:09:36,559
